This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) because it deals with natural language processing and text classification. It could also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) because it involves the collection and annotation of a large dataset of news articles. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) because it deals with the analysis of media and political partisanship. It may also be relevant to cs.LG (Machine Learning) because it involves the use of crowdsourcing and machine learning techniques for annotation and analysis. Finally, it could be categorized under cs.CY (Computers and Society) because it deals with the societal implications of media and political partisanship.
